{
  "stem": "16245.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Jews, of course, would always want to carry more than they could actually carry.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as they were being escorted, reasonably tolerantly by the police, they would, of course, drop all their possessions because they just couldn't carry them anymore.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Most of them were old.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you know, that's one of those disgusting memories.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When I see the vultures from the side street-- sidewalk, moving in and picking up the bits and pieces that the Jews dropped.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Quite a bit of gloating at the same time-- well, you know, you think they ought to have known better, but they didn't.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was one side of the story.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The other side were the Arrow Cross.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now, whoever they could lay their hands on, they killed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it-- it would happen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "For instance, at a round up of the Gestapo with Hungarian police, the Arrow Cross would lurk on at the edges.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Where the police weren't looking, they would grab a Jew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Kill him on the spot.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were much happier walking them down to the Danube and killing them there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You know, that's-- you could say it's a funny thing that to this day, that's always a problem of murder as, you know, to dispose of bodies.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And when they started in this business, and I think as I said before, most of these Arrow Cross were children of 14 and 15.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They would kill them on the banks of the river, and then toss them in the river and let them float to wherever.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the Danube froze over fairly early in the peace.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So they couldn't chuck the bodies into the water.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So what they did was they piled up the bodies in neat piles like fire wood.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
